Where are the tables?

1901
02:27:21,940 --> 02:27:23,264
Get out.

1902
02:27:24,661 --> 02:27:25,424
Hopp hopp

1903
02:27:25,484 --> 02:27:26,731
...luggage in wagons

1904
02:27:28,582 --> 02:27:31,222
Quick. Get out. Faster.

1905
02:27:31,661 --> 02:27:33,984
Leave the luggage in the wagons.

1906
02:27:34,660 --> 02:27:35,442
Faster.

1907
02:27:36,051 --> 02:27:38,315
Go faster.

1908
02:27:38,636 --> 02:27:39,945
Mama, where are we?

1909
02:27:44,230 --> 02:27:45,424
They're in Auschwitz.

1910
02:27:45,638 --> 02:27:48,030
The train was
never routed here: a paperwork mistake.

1911
02:27:55,902 --> 02:27:57,240
Hurry. Fast.

1912
02:27:57,297 --> 02:27:59,098
Remove your shoes.

1913
02:28:12,181 --> 02:28:13,101
Faster faster

1914
02:28:13,160 --> 02:28:14,208
Fold your clothing.

1915
02:28:17,259 --> 02:28:18,119
To the shower.

1916
02:28:18,177 --> 02:28:19,702
Remove your clothes. Move.

1917
02:28:19,777 --> 02:28:20,430
Move.

1918
02:28:20,488 --> 02:28:22,386
Stand up and go out.

1919
02:28:22,458 --> 02:28:23,723
Undress faster.

1920
02:28:23,783 --> 02:28:24,544
Faster.

1921
02:28:26,937 --> 02:28:28,236
Undress quickly.

1922
02:28:29,777 --> 02:28:31,094
Get soap and towel

1923
02:28:31,152 --> 02:28:33,609
and go to the shower for disinfection.

1924
02:28:33,982 --> 02:28:35,270
Undress quickly.

1925
02:28:39,824 --> 02:28:40,495
Faster.

1926
02:28:40,553 --> 02:28:42,504
Take that soap quickly.

1927
02:28:42,665 --> 02:28:45,198
Move out faster. Move.

1928
02:28:51,875 --> 02:28:52,806
Quickly quickly

1929
02:28:52,864 --> 02:28:53,886
Get in immediately. Faster.

1930
02:28:54,936 --> 02:28:56,900
Into the shower. Quick.

1931
02:28:56,976 --> 02:28:58,044
Faster.

1932
02:28:58,896 --> 02:29:00,574
Into the bath. Faster.

1933
02:29:03,534 --> 02:29:06,415
Faster faster

1934
02:29:08,033 --> 02:29:09,713
Quickly quickly

1935
02:29:10,534 --> 02:29:11,342
Come in.

1936
02:31:31,527 --> 02:31:32,694
Look down.

1937
02:31:36,005 --> 02:31:37,461
Hands on shoulders.

1938
02:31:38,613 --> 02:31:39,815
How old are you, mother?

1939
02:31:40,088 --> 02:31:41,333
Sixty-eight.

1940
02:31:41,812 --> 02:31:42,524
Cough for me, mother.

1941
02:31:42,583 --> 02:31:46,351
They say,
to fall against the fence is a kindness.

1942
02:31:46,776 --> 02:31:49,505
Don't kill yourself against the fence, Clara.

1943
02:31:49,809 --> 02:31:52,177
If you do,
we'll never know what happened to you.

1944
02:31:55,408 --> 02:31:56,461
How old are you, mother?

1945
02:31:56,630 --> 02:31:57,886
66, sir.

1946
02:31:58,007 --> 02:31:58,526
Sir?

1947
02:31:59,178 --> 02:31:59,881
Good morning

1948
02:32:00,047 --> 02:32:02,748
A mistake has
been made. We are not supposed to be here.

1949
02:32:03,007 --> 02:32:04,587
We work for Oskar Schindler.

1950
02:32:05,112 --> 02:32:06,350
We are Schindler jews.

1951
02:32:06,726 --> 02:32:07,949
Who is Oskar Schindler?

1952
02:32:08,357 --> 02:32:09,824
He had a factory in Krakow:

1953
02:32:10,068 --> 02:32:10,757
enamelware.

1954
02:32:12,163 --> 02:32:13,494
A pot maker.

1955
02:32:14,797 --> 02:32:15,954
How old are you, mother?

1956
02:32:20,949 --> 02:32:24,020
You are not
the only industrialist who needs labour

1957
02:32:26,406 --> 02:32:27,284
Herr Schindler.

1958
02:32:28,967 --> 02:32:31,732
I remember,
earlier this year, IG Farben ordered

1959
02:32:31,792 --> 02:32:33,473
a trainload of Hungarians

1960
02:32:34,350 --> 02:32:35,871
for its chemical factory.

1961
02:32:37,527 --> 02:32:40,133
The train came in through the archway

1962
02:32:41,297 --> 02:32:45,159
and the officer in charge
of the selection went immediately to work

1963
02:32:46,757 --> 02:32:48,524
and sent 2,000 of them

1964
02:32:49,244 --> 02:32:51,012
straight away to special treatment.

1965
02:32:53,446 --> 02:32:55,472
It is not my task to interfere with

1966
02:32:55,531 --> 02:32:57,255
the processes that take place down here.

1967
02:32:59,845 --> 02:33:01,486
Why do you think I can help you

1968
02:33:02,156 --> 02:33:03,931
if I can't help IG Farben?

1969
02:33:04,913 --> 02:33:06,470
Allow me to express the reason.

1970
02:33:16,244 --> 02:33:18,234
I'm not making any judgement about you.

1971
02:33:19,404 --> 02:33:22,044
It's
just that I know that in the coming months

1972
02:33:22,101 --> 02:33:24,087
we're all going to need portable wealth.

1973
02:33:28,204 --> 02:33:30,022
I could have you arrested.

1974
02:33:30,843 --> 02:33:32,684
I'm protected by powerful friends.

1975
02:33:33,510 --> 02:33:34,309
You should know that.

1976
02:33:38,324 --> 02:33:40,556
I do not say I am accepting them.

1977
02:33:42,204 --> 02:33:45,061
All I say is,
I'm not comfortable with them on the table.

1978
02:34:00,204 --> 02:34:02,200
I have a shipment coming in tomorrow.

1979
02:34:03,479 --> 02:34:05,324
I'll cut you 300 units from it:

1980
02:34:05,602 --> 02:34:06,357
new ones.

1981
02:34:07,718 --> 02:34:08,704
These are fresh.

1982
02:34:13,282 --> 02:34:15,530
The train comes, we turn it around.

1983
02:34:15,588 --> 02:34:16,811
Mmm yes yes

1984
02:34:16,870 --> 02:34:18,182
- It's yours.
- I understand.

1985
02:34:18,833 --> 02:34:19,551
I want these.

1986
02:34:23,858 --> 02:34:25,727
You shouldn't get stuck on names.

1987
02:34:33,843 --> 02:34:34,733
That's right.

1988
02:34:35,593 --> 02:34:37,057
It creates a lot of paperwork.

1989
